1
00:01:25,752 --> 00:01:27,337
Are you sure I can trust you?

2
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:30,381
I also cut my brother's hair for him.

3
00:01:30,465 --> 00:01:31,883
I'm the only one who can touch it.

4
00:01:35,094 --> 00:01:37,305
The sea should be here. Hello!

5
00:01:40,225 --> 00:01:42,143
He asked you to
cut his hair like that, right?

6
00:01:42,227 --> 00:01:43,061
No.

7
00:01:44,145 --> 00:01:45,647
I came up with that hairstyle.

8
00:01:46,231 --> 00:01:47,565
I don't want a mushroom haircut.

9
00:01:48,566 --> 00:01:49,567
It's too late.

10
00:01:50,151 --> 00:01:51,528
I have the scissors.

11
00:01:53,196 --> 00:01:54,948
Stay still if you want this to go well.

12
00:02:14,342 --> 00:02:15,218
It's all done.

13
00:03:14,402 --> 00:03:15,528
How do I look?

14
00:03:19,949 --> 00:03:20,950
You look pretty.

15
00:03:32,170 --> 00:03:34,339
I no longer need to listen to my mom

16
00:03:34,422 --> 00:03:35,715
now that I cut off my leash.

17
00:03:36,633 --> 00:03:38,134
So you wanted to escape from

18
00:03:38,718 --> 00:03:39,552
your mother?

19
00:03:41,304 --> 00:03:42,138
Yes.

20
00:03:42,931 --> 00:03:43,890
Now, I'm free.

21
00:03:46,184 --> 00:03:47,268
Congratulations.

22
00:03:49,812 --> 00:03:50,980
Don't congratulate me.

23
00:03:51,564 --> 00:03:52,440
I want a compliment.

24
00:03:58,780 --> 00:04:01,157
Good for you. I'm so proud of you.

25
00:04:04,494 --> 00:04:07,205
Now, let's go have fun wherever.
Whether it's to a mountain or a field.

26
00:04:08,331 --> 00:04:09,332
Like the Cheerful Dog?

27
00:04:09,415 --> 00:04:11,876
Yes, like the Cheerful Dog.

28
00:04:23,346 --> 00:04:27,976
CHAPTER 8
BEAUTY AND THE BEAST

29
00:04:28,559 --> 00:04:31,104
It is a flower

30
00:04:31,396 --> 00:04:34,232
Even if it blooms in the field
It is a flower

31
00:04:34,482 --> 00:04:37,735
It is a flower

32
00:04:38,486 --> 00:04:40,989
It is a flower

33
00:04:41,072 --> 00:04:43,032
They're all flowers

34
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:54,794
What... What happened to your long hair?

35
00:04:54,877 --> 00:04:56,129
I cut it.

36
00:04:57,171 --> 00:04:59,173
-What do you think?
-Long hair suits you better.

37
00:05:00,258 --> 00:05:02,218
What do you mean?
She looks better with short hair.

38
00:05:02,302 --> 00:05:03,553
No.

39
00:05:03,636 --> 00:05:06,014
She looked 100 to 1,000 times better
when her long, black hair

40
00:05:06,097 --> 00:05:08,474
used to come down
all the way to her waist.

41
00:05:08,558 --> 00:05:09,684
Why did she cut it?

42
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:12,103
-Why did you do that? Why?
-Sang-tae.

43
00:05:13,104 --> 00:05:15,940
Let me cut your hair today as well.
It's really long.

44
00:05:16,024 --> 00:05:17,608
You gave me a haircut on Wednesday.

45
00:05:17,692 --> 00:05:18,901
I only gave you a trim.

46
00:05:18,985 --> 00:05:20,987
Let's cut off a bit more today.
Now, eat up.

47
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:23,573
Okay. You looked better with long hair.

48
00:05:23,656 --> 00:05:25,616
Why did you do that?
You shouldn't have cut it off.

49
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:30,038
Why did you get such an ugly haircut?

50
00:05:30,872 --> 00:05:31,956
Why did you just kick me?

51
00:05:33,499 --> 00:05:35,293
-Me?
-Yes, that's right. You.

52
00:05:35,376 --> 00:05:37,420
You just kicked me three times.

53
00:05:37,503 --> 00:05:39,213
These darn quail eggs.

54
00:05:45,011 --> 00:05:46,012
Here.

55
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:56,481
I want a rolled omelet.

56
00:06:08,993 --> 00:06:09,869
Here.

57
00:06:18,711 --> 00:06:21,214
-Here.
-You should do it yourself.

58
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:23,466
You're not a baby.

59
00:06:24,175 --> 00:06:27,220
Your brother is so slow-witted.

60
00:06:28,846 --> 00:06:30,223
You mean he's too honest.

61
00:06:31,808 --> 00:06:33,434
Are you taking your brother's side?

62
00:06:34,268 --> 00:06:35,895
Of course. We're brothers.

63
00:06:38,439 --> 00:06:39,273
Hey.

64
00:06:42,193 --> 00:06:44,112
Come home as soon as you finish work.

65
00:06:44,445 --> 00:06:45,738
Come and spend time with me.

66
00:07:33,619 --> 00:07:35,830
From now on,
you're in charge of cutting my hair.

67
00:07:35,913 --> 00:07:36,747
Okay?

68
00:07:37,874 --> 00:07:39,125
Why not just go to a hair salon?

69
00:07:41,043 --> 00:07:42,879
I'm just like your brother.

70
00:07:42,962 --> 00:07:44,630
I don't like it
when other people touch me.

71
00:07:45,590 --> 00:07:47,800
But you're an exception.
Only you can touch me.

72
00:07:55,683 --> 00:07:57,059
Do I really look pretty?

73
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:04,317
Yes.

74
00:08:05,109 --> 00:08:06,027
You look pretty.

75
00:08:15,036 --> 00:08:16,037
I agree.

76
00:08:17,038 --> 00:08:18,581
I also think I'm really pretty.

77
00:08:21,501 --> 00:08:22,710
What was that laugh for?

78
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:26,464
Don't fight with Sang-tae.
Make sure you get along.

79
00:08:27,882 --> 00:08:28,841
I'll see you.

80
00:08:34,472 --> 00:08:36,349
Come home quickly.
If you're late, I'll kill you.

81
00:09:15,471 --> 00:09:17,265
-Hello.
-Hello.

82
00:09:21,936 --> 00:09:25,022
KO MUN-YEONG'S FAIRY TALE CLASS
PUT ON PAUSE TEMPORARILY

83
00:09:34,657 --> 00:09:35,866
Gosh, you scared me.

84
00:09:36,951 --> 00:09:38,452
Do I look that bad?

85
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:42,665
I look like a zombie.

86
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:45,209
Did something happen at night?

87
00:09:46,419 --> 00:09:47,378
Do you have a concealer?

88
00:09:48,045 --> 00:09:49,255
-What's that?
-Maybe a cushion?

89
00:09:49,338 --> 00:09:51,465
-The cushions are in the lounge.
-No, a cushion compact.

90
00:09:53,634 --> 00:09:54,468
Forget it.

91
00:09:56,804 --> 00:09:59,056
Did something happen with a patient?
Who was it?

92
00:09:59,515 --> 00:10:00,683
Mr. Ko Dae-hwan.

93
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:02,226
Why? What happened?

94
00:10:04,103 --> 00:10:06,814
He had a seizure last night again.
It was a complete nightmare.

95
00:10:07,481 --> 00:10:10,067
He came out to the hallway
with his eyes rolling upwards.

96
00:10:10,151 --> 00:10:12,361
Then he started foaming at the mouth
and had spasms.

97
00:10:14,739 --> 00:10:16,490
I didn't get to sleep a wink.

98
00:10:17,825 --> 00:10:21,287
Gosh, why does this happen
every time I'm on night duty?

99
00:10:21,495 --> 00:10:22,705
Why?

100
00:10:31,380 --> 00:10:32,256
My goodness.

101
00:10:35,801 --> 00:10:37,053
Do you think he'll be okay?

102
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:39,930
I'm worried he might have
another brain tumor.

103
00:10:40,139 --> 00:10:41,974
He kept talking gibberish all night.

104
00:10:42,141 --> 00:10:43,559
Don't worry too much.

105
00:10:44,852 --> 00:10:46,562
I bet you didn't get any sleep last night.

106
00:10:46,729 --> 00:10:48,898
I was actually thinking about
skipping meditation class

107
00:10:48,981 --> 00:10:50,650
and get some good sleep instead.

108
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:52,234
You should do that. Here.

109
00:11:00,826 --> 00:11:01,661
Get some sleep.

110
00:11:12,713 --> 00:11:13,923
Mr. Moon.

111
00:11:15,508 --> 00:11:16,801
Mr. Ko has drooled too much.

112
00:11:17,802 --> 00:11:18,928
Can you help him get changed?

113
00:11:19,804 --> 00:11:20,721
Sure.

114
00:11:26,644 --> 00:11:28,646
That woman...

115
00:11:31,357 --> 00:11:32,650
sang

116
00:11:33,442 --> 00:11:34,902
a song.

117
00:11:35,861 --> 00:11:37,947
What song?

118
00:11:38,531 --> 00:11:39,698
"Oh My Darling, Clementine."

119
00:11:41,659 --> 00:11:42,910
I'm sure

120
00:11:44,787 --> 00:11:45,955
she's dead.

121
00:11:51,919 --> 00:11:53,421
But that woman

122
00:11:55,881 --> 00:11:57,716
is here.

123
00:12:00,261 --> 00:12:01,512
Who are you

124
00:12:02,805 --> 00:12:03,639
talking about?

125
00:12:07,893 --> 00:12:09,937
She's dead.

126
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,649
But she's here.

127
00:12:21,365 --> 00:12:24,368
WHAT IS THE TRUTH BEHIND WRITER
KO MUN-YEONG'S DISAPPEARANCE?

128
00:12:24,452 --> 00:12:26,287
KO MUN-YEONG IS LOOKING AFTER
HER SICK FATHER

129
00:12:26,370 --> 00:12:27,621
IS SHE PLANNING TO RETIRE?

130
00:12:31,083 --> 00:12:33,002
She's pretending to be a kind daughter.

131
00:12:33,085 --> 00:12:34,837
I bet she doesn't even care.

132
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:37,840
She needs to become a better person first.

133
00:12:37,923 --> 00:12:40,342
A fairy tale writer who cusses
doesn't deserve to write.

134
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:42,636
I really regret having read her books.

135
00:12:43,137 --> 00:12:46,724
I want to gather these insects
and spray pesticide on them.

136
00:12:47,766 --> 00:12:49,101
Darn it.

137
00:12:49,185 --> 00:12:51,729
I used to have tons of fans.
Where in the world are they?

138
00:13:00,696 --> 00:13:03,115
Actually, my fan is right here.

139
00:13:03,199 --> 00:13:06,660
Don't forget to ventilate the room
after you spray pesticide.

140
00:13:06,744 --> 00:13:10,789
But if you want to kill insects properly,
electric fly swatters are the best.

141
00:13:11,957 --> 00:13:14,585
Sang-tae, why do you like my fairy tales?

142
00:13:16,670 --> 00:13:18,339
Because you wrote them.

143
00:13:20,966 --> 00:13:23,636
So you like me, not my fairy tales.

144
00:13:24,428 --> 00:13:26,096
-Why do you like me?
-Because you're pretty.

145
00:13:28,682 --> 00:13:30,476
What do you like about me?

146
00:13:32,144 --> 00:13:34,605
Your hair. Your long hair.

147
00:13:35,064 --> 00:13:37,316
Your long, black hair
that came all the way to your waist.

148
00:13:37,399 --> 00:13:39,235
It was so pretty. Gosh.

149
00:13:39,777 --> 00:13:42,071
-You cut it off. You shouldn't have.
-End of meeting.

150
00:13:44,865 --> 00:13:46,367
We never started a meeting.

151
00:13:46,450 --> 00:13:48,661
How can you end a meeting
when we never even started one?

152
00:13:48,744 --> 00:13:50,204
You give me a headache.

153
00:13:50,287 --> 00:13:52,122
-Let's have a meeting later.
-"Later?"

154
00:13:52,414 --> 00:13:53,666
Later... Later.

155
00:13:54,041 --> 00:13:56,085
You mean sometime before you die?

156
00:13:56,460 --> 00:13:59,129
No, I need to get a camping car.

157
00:13:59,213 --> 00:14:01,507
I need to receive a camping car.

158
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:08,389
Did you get the information I asked for?

159
00:14:11,809 --> 00:14:15,437
I know you told me
this is all part of work,

160
00:14:16,021 --> 00:14:18,315
but I felt so uneasy
about doing a background search.

161
00:14:18,399 --> 00:14:19,525
Why?

162
00:14:20,150 --> 00:14:22,152
You're good at doing that.

163
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:26,574
If you hadn't done a background search
on that caregiver for Mun-yeong--

164
00:14:26,657 --> 00:14:28,576
Her name is Nam Ju-ri.
She's currently single.

165
00:14:29,076 --> 00:14:31,370
She met Moon Gang-tae
when they worked together

166
00:14:31,453 --> 00:14:32,913
at the same hospital a year ago.

167
00:14:34,456 --> 00:14:35,833
They haven't known each other long.

168
00:14:35,916 --> 00:14:38,252
Her father died due to an illness
when she was little.

169
00:14:38,335 --> 00:14:39,795
Oh, dear.

170
00:14:39,879 --> 00:14:42,715
And her mother used to cook
for construction workers.

171
00:14:42,798 --> 00:14:44,675
My goodness, she had a tough life.

172
00:14:45,259 --> 00:14:48,095
Right now, she's working as a cook
at OK Psychiatric Hospital.

173
00:14:48,178 --> 00:14:50,306
And the daughter and mother
are living together

174
00:14:50,389 --> 00:14:52,391
at a two-story house
with a mortgage to pay off.

175
00:14:52,474 --> 00:14:54,435
The Moon brothers live
in the rooftop house.

176
00:14:54,518 --> 00:14:57,980
And their friend who runs a pizza place
lives in the basement.

177
00:14:58,397 --> 00:15:01,066
And apparently, the owner of the house
gives them meals for free.

178
00:15:02,484 --> 00:15:04,028
They're practically lodgers.

179
00:15:04,820 --> 00:15:05,654
Mr. Lee.

180
00:15:06,655 --> 00:15:07,740
Do you like that nurse?

181
00:15:09,491 --> 00:15:13,662
Hey, why are you so quick-witted
when it comes to stuff like this?

182
00:15:13,746 --> 00:15:15,039
Why can't you be like this with work?

183
00:15:21,211 --> 00:15:22,212
Hey.

184
00:15:23,339 --> 00:15:24,757
Be honest with me.

185
00:15:25,466 --> 00:15:26,592
About what?

186
00:15:27,301 --> 00:15:30,137
Between me and that caregiver...

187
00:15:30,763 --> 00:15:32,014
Who do you think is better?

188
00:15:32,097 --> 00:15:33,265
For a romantic relationship?

189
00:15:33,349 --> 00:15:36,185
I'm taller and bigger than him.

190
00:15:36,268 --> 00:15:39,063
And think about
my social position and maturity.

191
00:15:39,563 --> 00:15:41,315
Aren't I much better than him?

192
00:15:42,733 --> 00:15:45,152
But you lack the most important trait.

193
00:15:47,529 --> 00:15:48,364
What's that?

194
00:15:50,574 --> 00:15:52,826
This. Your face.

195
00:15:52,910 --> 00:15:56,246
My gosh. You little!

196
00:16:19,395 --> 00:16:20,396
How do I look?

197
00:16:21,689 --> 00:16:22,690
You look pretty.

198
00:16:29,363 --> 00:16:31,949
I must be crazy.

199
00:17:16,535 --> 00:17:19,997
Hey, can I talk to Ms. Park Ok-ran?

200
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:22,624
Yes, right now.

201
00:17:25,836 --> 00:17:26,795
Come in.

202
00:17:27,421 --> 00:17:28,505
DIRECTOR'S OFFICE

203
00:17:30,132 --> 00:17:31,258
My goodness.

204
00:17:32,259 --> 00:17:34,428
Hello, Ms. Park.

205
00:17:35,179 --> 00:17:37,181
You can sit over here.

206
00:17:41,643 --> 00:17:42,644
Stay.

207
00:17:42,728 --> 00:17:43,562
Just stay.

208
00:17:45,564 --> 00:17:48,901
My goodness, you look great these days.

209
00:17:48,984 --> 00:17:50,903
I guess the medicine is working.

210
00:17:52,821 --> 00:17:54,323
Why did you want to see me?

211
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:58,660
I wanted to ask you something.

212
00:17:59,661 --> 00:18:03,624
By any chance,
did you happen to see Mr. Ko Dae-hwan

213
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:05,626
in the hallway last night

214
00:18:06,752 --> 00:18:08,420
at around midnight?

215
00:18:10,506 --> 00:18:11,465
I did

216
00:18:12,341 --> 00:18:14,551
go to the bathroom at that hour.

217
00:18:15,969 --> 00:18:16,804
But I didn't see him.

218
00:18:22,518 --> 00:18:26,230
By any chance, did you sing a song
when you went to the bathroom?

219
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:28,023
A song?

220
00:18:29,608 --> 00:18:30,442
What song?

221
00:18:32,027 --> 00:18:35,781
Ever since he regained consciousness
he keeps saying the same thing.

222
00:18:37,032 --> 00:18:38,575
What was it... You know...

223
00:18:38,659 --> 00:18:39,493
Right!

224
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:42,704
"Oh My Darling, Clementine."

225
00:18:43,956 --> 00:18:46,750
He keeps saying that he heard that song.

226
00:18:48,752 --> 00:18:55,634
In a cavern, in a canyon,

227
00:18:55,884 --> 00:18:58,720
Excavating for a mine

228
00:18:59,263 --> 00:19:02,266
...sang a song.

229
00:19:03,809 --> 00:19:05,435
"Oh My Darling, Clementine."

230
00:19:06,395 --> 00:19:09,231
Lived a miner

231
00:19:09,815 --> 00:19:13,318
forty-niner,

232
00:19:14,945 --> 00:19:17,573
-I'm not a ghost.
-"A ghost"?

233
00:19:17,656 --> 00:19:20,200
Yoo Seon-hae,
that woman who used to be a shaman,

234
00:19:20,576 --> 00:19:21,743
keeps talking nonsense.

235
00:19:22,995 --> 00:19:25,581
She keeps saying a ghost shows up at night

236
00:19:26,206 --> 00:19:27,875
and sings at the end of the hallway.

237
00:19:33,463 --> 00:19:34,381
But

238
00:19:35,299 --> 00:19:37,050
I'm not a ghost.

239
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:41,054
Of course you're not a ghost.

240
00:19:42,973 --> 00:19:44,099
So you didn't sing that song?

241
00:19:46,518 --> 00:19:47,352
No, I didn't.

242
00:19:49,229 --> 00:19:50,522
Okay then.

243
00:20:04,995 --> 00:20:06,496
Why are you smiling?

244
00:20:07,581 --> 00:20:08,415
It's just that

245
00:20:09,791 --> 00:20:11,418
no one's really paid attention to me

246
00:20:12,502 --> 00:20:14,880
even though I've been here
for a few months.

247
00:20:16,548 --> 00:20:18,133
But now, people are paying attention.

248
00:20:21,929 --> 00:20:22,763
How interesting.

249
00:20:29,102 --> 00:20:30,687
OK PSYCHIATRIC HOSPITAL

250
00:20:36,026 --> 00:20:42,199
You are lost and gone forever,

251
00:20:42,407 --> 00:20:48,080
Dreadful sorry Clementine

252
00:20:48,997 --> 00:20:50,082
It's that song.

253
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:53,460
Why do you think she lied?

254
00:20:56,922 --> 00:20:57,923
I don't know.

255
00:20:59,841 --> 00:21:00,676
But

256
00:21:01,802 --> 00:21:03,679
why are you asking me?

257
00:21:04,263 --> 00:21:07,766
Ms. Ko Mun-yeong
is Mr. Ko Dae-hwan's only guardian.

258
00:21:08,475 --> 00:21:11,019
And right now, you're pretty much

259
00:21:11,603 --> 00:21:13,230
Ms. Ko Mun-yeong's guardian.

260
00:21:14,773 --> 00:21:16,275
So it's kind of your business as well.

261
00:21:17,693 --> 00:21:19,069
I don't think it is.

262
00:21:24,199 --> 00:21:25,200
Chew on this.

263
00:21:26,743 --> 00:21:29,871
Chewing on something
helps you prevent dementia.

264
00:21:32,457 --> 00:21:35,210
It seems like something strange
is happening at our hospital.

265
00:21:36,503 --> 00:21:39,256
Let's keep this between you and me
for the time being.

266
00:21:40,799 --> 00:21:43,427
And during that time,
I'd like you to keep a close eye

267
