542
00:41:18,893 --> 00:41:19,894
We're three brothers.

543
00:41:19,977 --> 00:41:21,645
Mang-tae, Gang-tae, and Sang-tae, right?

544
00:41:22,521 --> 00:41:23,939
-Both of you.
-It's mine!

545
00:41:24,023 --> 00:41:25,733
No, I told you that
Mang-tae is mine. Mine!

546
00:41:25,816 --> 00:41:28,152
-No, it's mine!
-Mang-tae is mine.

547
00:41:28,235 --> 00:41:29,904
-It's mine.
-Mang-tae is mine!

548
00:41:29,987 --> 00:41:31,113
-Mang-tae is mine!
-Be quiet!

549
00:41:48,130 --> 00:41:49,131
Both of you, give it back.

550
00:41:54,512 --> 00:41:55,596
One.

551
00:41:56,305 --> 00:41:57,181
Two.

552
00:41:59,767 --> 00:42:00,935
Three.

553
00:42:01,018 --> 00:42:02,311
Hey!

554
00:42:02,603 --> 00:42:04,563
Go away! I hate you!

555
00:42:04,647 --> 00:42:05,981
-I hate you.
-Hey!

556
00:42:06,857 --> 00:42:09,109
I hate Ms. Ko Mun-yeong.

557
00:42:09,693 --> 00:42:13,405
Ms. Ko Mun-yeong is vicious.
She's a real fighter.

558
00:42:14,406 --> 00:42:15,282
Ko Mun-yeong...

559
00:42:15,366 --> 00:42:16,325
You too. Give it back.

560
00:42:16,408 --> 00:42:19,411
You gave it to me! You can't take it back!

561
00:42:19,495 --> 00:42:22,289
I told you not to fight with Sang-tae.
Anyway, give it to me.

562
00:42:25,292 --> 00:42:26,418
Give it back, now.

563
00:42:28,754 --> 00:42:29,630
There!

564
00:42:47,022 --> 00:42:48,649
You jerk! You petty asshole!

565
00:42:48,732 --> 00:42:49,984
You petty bastard!

566
00:42:50,067 --> 00:42:51,443
I can't believe that petty bastard!

567
00:42:57,992 --> 00:43:00,160
Sang-tae, come out.

568
00:43:01,078 --> 00:43:02,037
You should get changed.

569
00:43:06,667 --> 00:43:08,586
If you don't want to come out,
just open the door.

570
00:43:19,471 --> 00:43:20,556
You know that Mang-tae

571
00:43:22,933 --> 00:43:24,435
can't catch the butterflies anyway.

572
00:43:25,811 --> 00:43:27,980
Mang-tae can't catch the butterflies.

573
00:43:29,398 --> 00:43:30,524
What did you say?

574
00:43:31,400 --> 00:43:32,484
I can't really hear you.

575
00:43:36,655 --> 00:43:38,616
He's of no use
if he can't catch the butterflies.

576
00:43:39,950 --> 00:43:40,868
Exactly.

577
00:43:41,827 --> 00:43:44,121
You shoved it into the drawer
and forgot about it,

578
00:43:44,997 --> 00:43:46,290
so I gave it to Ms. Ko.

579
00:43:51,920 --> 00:43:53,797
I'm sorry I didn't ask
for your permission first.

580
00:43:54,465 --> 00:43:56,925
But when you don't need something,

581
00:43:57,885 --> 00:43:59,970
it's nice to offer it
to someone who needs it.

582
00:44:01,513 --> 00:44:02,348
"Offer"?

583
00:44:02,431 --> 00:44:04,600
Yes, that's right.

584
00:44:05,351 --> 00:44:06,352
But...

585
00:44:07,394 --> 00:44:10,022
if I give all my stuff
to people who need them,

586
00:44:10,773 --> 00:44:11,607
what about me?

587
00:44:13,901 --> 00:44:15,527
What will I have left?

588
00:44:23,577 --> 00:44:24,495
You will

589
00:44:25,704 --> 00:44:26,830
always have me.

590
00:44:28,165 --> 00:44:30,334
Forget Mang-tae. You have Gang-tae.

591
00:44:31,960 --> 00:44:33,921
Ms. Ko is alone, so she needs Mang-tae.

592
00:44:34,004 --> 00:44:36,548
Then will you let her have Mang-tae?

593
00:44:36,632 --> 00:44:39,385
Yes, she can have him.
She can have Mang-tae, not Gang-tae.

594
00:44:43,389 --> 00:44:45,015
She can have Mang-tae, not Gang-tae.

595
00:44:48,727 --> 00:44:49,561
Yes.

596
00:44:51,563 --> 00:44:53,732
She can have Mang-tae, not Gang-tae.

597
00:44:53,816 --> 00:44:54,942
Yes, she can take him.

598
00:45:10,541 --> 00:45:11,375
Hey.

599
00:45:14,420 --> 00:45:16,046
I can't sleep because I'm fuming mad.

600
00:45:16,130 --> 00:45:17,965
What did I do wrong?

601
00:45:18,549 --> 00:45:20,134
Sang-tae said you could have him.

602
00:45:21,844 --> 00:45:22,761
Mang-tae.

603
00:45:23,929 --> 00:45:25,180
Mang-tae is all yours now.

604
00:45:28,767 --> 00:45:30,811
Whatever. It was mine to begin with.

605
00:45:31,395 --> 00:45:33,355
Try to stay calm
even when Sang-tae gets worked up.

606
00:45:33,439 --> 00:45:35,732
-Don't give me orders.
-It's not an order.

607
00:45:39,278 --> 00:45:40,362
I'm asking you for a favor.

608
00:45:48,162 --> 00:45:49,913
But how can I suppress my anger
and stay calm?

609
00:45:53,709 --> 00:45:55,419
Tell me. You're an expert at it.

610
00:45:57,588 --> 00:45:59,715
I saw you do it
when I cut your hand with a knife.

611
00:46:01,008 --> 00:46:04,303
Even when that man grabbed your brother
by the hair at the bookstore

612
00:46:05,179 --> 00:46:08,140
and when your brother
beat the crap out of you on the floor.

613
00:46:09,141 --> 00:46:11,351
You just kept it all inside
and let him beat you up.

614
00:46:14,271 --> 00:46:15,856
How do you do that?

615
00:46:17,649 --> 00:46:19,067
If I just suck it up,

616
00:46:21,820 --> 00:46:23,572
nothing will happen.

617
00:46:25,491 --> 00:46:27,117
If I let my emotions get the better of me

618
00:46:27,701 --> 00:46:29,286
without thinking about the consequences,

619
00:46:32,247 --> 00:46:34,333
Sang-tae and I wouldn't have
this kind of relationship.

620
00:46:36,126 --> 00:46:37,794
Keeping it all inside and enduring it

621
00:46:39,963 --> 00:46:41,548
is the only way

622
00:46:43,175 --> 00:46:44,593
I can protect Sang-tae.

623
00:46:48,222 --> 00:46:49,681
I think that's why we're meant to be.

624
00:46:54,937 --> 00:46:56,563
You're patient,

625
00:46:56,939 --> 00:46:58,190
and I'm volatile.

626
00:46:59,900 --> 00:47:01,443
Like a bomb and its safety pin.

627
00:47:02,277 --> 00:47:04,196
We go hand in hand.

628
00:47:05,781 --> 00:47:07,157
We're meant to be together.

629
00:47:10,244 --> 00:47:12,204
How many guys
do you think you're meant to be with?

630
00:47:12,996 --> 00:47:13,830
What do you mean?

631
00:47:14,623 --> 00:47:16,458
Why don't you go ask your "handsome" fan?

632
00:47:16,542 --> 00:47:17,501
"Handsome"?

633
00:47:25,551 --> 00:47:26,385
You mean, this pen?

634
00:47:29,304 --> 00:47:30,305
What do you think?

635
00:47:31,431 --> 00:47:32,724
Isn't it so handsome?

636
00:47:33,934 --> 00:47:36,311
Just look at this shape. It's perfect.

637
00:47:39,064 --> 00:47:40,357
But you know,

638
00:47:46,280 --> 00:47:48,323
you're much more handsome

639
00:47:49,241 --> 00:47:50,534
than this pen.

640
00:47:52,035 --> 00:47:53,870
Gosh, what are you doing?

641
00:47:55,455 --> 00:47:56,873
So don't be jealous.

642
00:48:00,168 --> 00:48:01,587
What? I'm not jealous.

643
00:48:02,087 --> 00:48:03,505
I'm sleepy.

644
00:48:05,173 --> 00:48:06,592
Go upstairs and sleep.

645
00:48:06,675 --> 00:48:09,094
I don't want to. Mang-tae is here.

646
00:48:10,846 --> 00:48:12,014
Relax, will you?

647
00:48:18,270 --> 00:48:20,731
By the way, did Director O call you?

648
00:48:21,481 --> 00:48:22,899
About resuming your class.

649
00:48:23,859 --> 00:48:25,068
He did.

650
00:48:25,652 --> 00:48:26,486
I see.

651
00:48:28,071 --> 00:48:29,823
They received many requests
from the patients.

652
00:48:31,450 --> 00:48:32,284
I guess

653
00:48:33,619 --> 00:48:34,828
they all liked your class.

654
00:50:30,736 --> 00:50:31,820
My mustache!

655
00:50:33,905 --> 00:50:35,365
Where did my mustache go?

656
00:50:36,408 --> 00:50:37,617
Oh, that.

657
00:50:38,285 --> 00:50:39,286
I shaved it off.

658
00:50:42,706 --> 00:50:43,540
What?

659
00:50:44,374 --> 00:50:45,208
Why?

660
00:50:46,334 --> 00:50:47,210
Well...

661
00:50:47,711 --> 00:50:48,545
Damn you!

662
00:50:50,672 --> 00:50:53,133
How dare you touch my mustache?

663
00:50:53,216 --> 00:50:55,510
You're partially responsible. Let go!

664
00:50:57,596 --> 00:50:58,597
-You little...
-What?

665
00:51:02,309 --> 00:51:03,852
Wait, hold on. No.

666
00:51:04,227 --> 00:51:06,730
No. Please! No!

667
00:51:09,608 --> 00:51:10,817
Ko Mun-yeong...

668
00:51:10,901 --> 00:51:13,195
-You bitch.
-I can't focus because of him.

669
00:51:13,987 --> 00:51:16,323
Seriously, what a pain in the butt!

670
00:52:15,715 --> 00:52:16,800
You had gum stuck on it?

671
00:52:16,883 --> 00:52:20,387
Yes, it was glued on it.

672
00:52:21,429 --> 00:52:22,639
My goodness.

673
00:52:23,890 --> 00:52:26,560
You look so handsome
without your mustache.

674
00:52:26,852 --> 00:52:28,770
Jae-su, I'm glad you shaved it off.

675
00:52:31,815 --> 00:52:34,442
Thank you so much, Jae-su.

676
00:52:35,443 --> 00:52:36,278
My gosh.

677
00:52:36,444 --> 00:52:38,363
Didn't he lash out at me
for shaving it off?

678
00:52:45,579 --> 00:52:46,872
What are you doing, Seung-jae?

679
00:52:50,125 --> 00:52:51,710
Good morning, Ju-ri.

680
00:52:52,294 --> 00:52:54,462
Did I wake you up?

681
00:52:54,546 --> 00:52:55,422
No.

682
00:52:55,922 --> 00:52:57,883
Why are you cleaning out of the blue?

683
00:52:57,966 --> 00:53:01,720
Oh, I figured I should do something
to help out

684
00:53:01,803 --> 00:53:03,722
while staying here with you.

685
00:53:04,055 --> 00:53:06,266
I'll be in charge of cleaning the room.

686
00:53:07,392 --> 00:53:10,604
Just pretend I'm not here.

687
00:53:10,687 --> 00:53:12,397
Don't mind me.

688
00:53:19,696 --> 00:53:20,906
Ju-ri.

689
00:53:21,615 --> 00:53:22,949
Do you notice anything different?

690
00:53:23,033 --> 00:53:25,160
You looked better with a mustache.
Why did you shave?

691
00:53:29,539 --> 00:53:31,291
Here, have some meat.

692
00:53:33,460 --> 00:53:36,630
Sang-tae can be a handful,

693
00:53:36,713 --> 00:53:40,050
but he can draw very well,

694
00:53:40,258 --> 00:53:41,760
so please take good care of him.

695
00:53:41,843 --> 00:53:45,221
Then I'll make sure
there's always meat on the table.

696
00:53:45,305 --> 00:53:48,183
My gosh. Don't you worry, ma'am.

697
00:53:49,267 --> 00:53:51,561
I have to say, this is a feast.

698
00:53:51,645 --> 00:53:53,271
I don't even know what I should eat first.

699
00:53:55,357 --> 00:53:56,232
The soup is too salty.

700
00:54:06,409 --> 00:54:07,327
Eat up.

701
00:54:11,039 --> 00:54:13,375
I must say, you're very impressive.

702
00:54:13,458 --> 00:54:16,878
You're still young,
yet you have your own publishing company.

703
00:54:18,546 --> 00:54:20,382
I run my own pizzeria
despite my young age--

704
00:54:20,507 --> 00:54:21,716
Ms. Kang.

705
00:54:22,133 --> 00:54:26,429
I know I'm only paying
200,000 won a month to stay here,

706
00:54:27,138 --> 00:54:29,766
but I'll get back on my feet again soon

707
00:54:29,849 --> 00:54:33,436
and make sure I repay your kindness
a thousandfold.

708
00:54:33,520 --> 00:54:37,023
Then finish your food quickly.
Let's put it down in writing.

709
00:54:39,442 --> 00:54:40,276
My gosh.

710
00:54:49,119 --> 00:54:52,539
What is it now? Why are you in a bad mood?

711
00:54:52,622 --> 00:54:55,083
Why did you ask Mr. Lee
what his parents do?

712
00:54:55,166 --> 00:54:57,043
He'll stay with us for a while.

713
00:54:57,127 --> 00:54:59,129
I can't even ask him about his family?

714
00:54:59,462 --> 00:55:02,132
It bothers me
that you seem so intrigued by him.

715
00:55:02,716 --> 00:55:04,801
Because he's interested in you.

716
00:55:05,427 --> 00:55:06,261
How did you know?

717
00:55:06,344 --> 00:55:08,221
When you get to my age, you'll understand.

718
00:55:08,304 --> 00:55:10,557
There are some things
that you just know when you're older.

719
00:55:11,975 --> 00:55:13,268
If you know that,

720
00:55:13,935 --> 00:55:15,895
don't lead him on.

721
00:55:16,479 --> 00:55:19,065
He's hardworking and cheerful.

722
00:55:19,357 --> 00:55:21,026
He seems like a responsible guy.
So why not?

723
00:55:21,109 --> 00:55:24,362
Mom, you know why I'm being like this.

724
00:55:25,363 --> 00:55:27,282
Yes, I know. That's why I'm saying this.

725
00:55:28,074 --> 00:55:31,369
That guy won't even reciprocate
my dear daughter's feelings.

726
00:55:31,661 --> 00:55:32,871
I, too, hate him for that.

727
00:55:34,706 --> 00:55:35,957
I hate him,

728
00:55:37,208 --> 00:55:38,334
but I also feel bad for him.

729
00:55:40,378 --> 00:55:42,964
However, you matter a lot more to me.

730
00:55:44,257 --> 00:55:47,343
You told me to keep on chasing after him
even if he rejects me.

731
00:55:47,844 --> 00:55:49,679
I'm worried that
you're going to follow him

732
00:55:49,763 --> 00:55:52,432
to the edge of a cliff
if I let you continue to chase after him.

733
00:56:03,193 --> 00:56:04,235
Hello.

734
00:56:04,319 --> 00:56:05,987
Oh, that's your live-in cook.

735
00:56:06,571 --> 00:56:08,615
The three of you came together?

736
00:56:08,698 --> 00:56:11,868
Yes, I'm here to work on the mural.
Gang-tae has his day shift,

737
00:56:11,951 --> 00:56:13,703
and Ms. Ko has her class.

738
00:56:14,329 --> 00:56:15,830
-Is that right?
-Yes.

739
00:56:16,498 --> 00:56:17,582
You got a haircut.

740
00:56:18,166 --> 00:56:19,167
It looks nice.

741
00:56:20,752 --> 00:56:22,462
He gave me a haircut.

742
00:56:26,508 --> 00:56:27,884
You cut her hair?

743
00:56:27,967 --> 00:56:30,887
Why did you do that?
She looks prettier with long hair.

744
00:56:32,972 --> 00:56:34,808
Come over when you have some time.

745
00:56:34,891 --> 00:56:36,392
I'll make some food for you.

746
00:56:38,228 --> 00:56:40,021
I don't think
your daughter likes the idea.

747
00:56:42,357 --> 00:56:43,733
She takes after me,

748
00:56:43,817 --> 00:56:45,026
so she can't hide her feelings.

749
00:56:47,445 --> 00:56:49,614
Don't worry.
Just come over and have some food.

750
00:56:49,948 --> 00:56:52,158
You two can fight again
if you have any energy left.

751
00:56:52,242 --> 00:56:54,702
Even better if you girls can make up
after the fight.

752
00:56:56,663 --> 00:56:57,914
We have to go.

753
00:57:08,049 --> 00:57:09,300
Do you like that two-faced girl?

754
00:57:10,343 --> 00:57:11,261
What?

755
00:57:11,761 --> 00:57:14,681
-Why did you cut Ms. Ko's hair? Why?
-Sang-tae, that's...

756
00:57:14,764 --> 00:57:16,432
Or do you have a crush
on your live-in cook?

757
00:57:17,267 --> 00:57:18,393
Stop talking nonsense.

758
00:57:18,476 --> 00:57:20,019
Then why did you unlink my arm?

759
00:57:20,103 --> 00:57:21,604
Why should I link arms with you?

760
00:57:21,688 --> 00:57:23,064
Because we go hand in hand.

761
00:57:23,690 --> 00:57:24,858
Let go.

762
00:57:25,024 --> 00:57:27,318
The bomb needs its safety pin.

763
00:57:27,402 --> 00:57:31,156
Let me... Let me join.
I want to link arms too.

764
00:57:33,158 --> 00:57:34,826
-Okay?
-Look ahead of you,

765
00:57:34,909 --> 00:57:36,369
or you'll trip and fall. Look ahead.

766
00:57:36,453 --> 00:57:37,537
-Okay?
-Look ahead of you.

767
00:57:37,620 --> 00:57:39,581
Look ahead of you,
or you'll trip and fall.

768
00:57:48,214 --> 00:57:50,717
Gosh, I thought you'd be mad at me
and refuse to teach.

769
00:57:50,800 --> 00:57:52,469
I was so worried yesterday.

770
00:57:53,678 --> 00:57:57,140
Well, I heard the patients
miss my class like crazy.

771
00:57:57,807 --> 00:57:58,766
Did Mr. Moon say that?

772
00:58:00,351 --> 00:58:03,480
I guess he was too embarrassed
to tell you that he threatened me.

773
00:58:05,190 --> 00:58:06,566
He threatened you?

774
00:58:07,066 --> 00:58:09,444
He said I'd better resume
the fairy tale class,

775
00:58:09,527 --> 00:58:12,113
or he wouldn't do anything
I tell him to do.

776
00:58:12,197 --> 00:58:14,908
He glared at me and gave me an ultimatum.

777
00:58:16,034 --> 00:58:17,202
Why did he do that?

778
00:58:17,494 --> 00:58:21,164
I guess he wants to see you
even when he's working.

779
00:58:25,084 --> 00:58:26,878
There's something I want to ask you.

780
00:58:29,130 --> 00:58:30,089
Do you,

781
00:58:31,341 --> 00:58:35,303
by any chance,
know our patient, Ms. Park Ok-ran?

